# Dogfood line 2026-07-16 (the auto-apply tuning wave). Typed:
#   "Ef allir krakkarnir ery í simanum hverbjg á eg að hega talað vð þau"
# Intended fixes, all auto-applied after the wave:
#   ery → eru        (adjacent-key sub, ordinary margin)
#   simanum → símanum (restoration past the BÍN-valid skeleton via the
#                      oblique-only dominance fallback — "simanum" is a
#                      þgf-only form of BÍN's variant lemma "simi", no
#                      nominative reading, never a word typed on purpose)
#   hverbjg → hvernig (deep beam, two substitutions)
#   eg → ég          (2-char restoration; minAutocorrectLength 3 → 2 with
#                      the short-token typicality floor)
#   vð → við         (2-char omission repair, extreme-common winner)
# "hega": Jökull's ground truth = "geta" (h→g + g→t, both cheap subs).
# The context-vouched double-sub tier now surfaces geta in the bar, but
# auto-apply correctly refuses: "gefa" (equally cheap, equally blessed by
# the "að" bigram) ties within margin — mid-word "að ge_a" is genuinely
# ambiguous between give/be-able; offer-both is the honest outcome.
# verbatim-led is the correct behavior there.
# ============================================================

