# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Wave 30 — deep-decode mash recovery (the eotthbap→eitthvað class).
# Fast-typing mashes with 2-3 adjacent-key substitutions whose taps mostly
# resolved to the WRONG key's center (motor-plan aim errors, not touch
# noise). The tapless engine already decoded this class — the per-tap LLR
# was pricing even taps that LEAN toward the intended key above the static
# geometry cost, so with real coordinates the decode blew every cap. The
# TAP offsets below are the REAL recorded coordinates from the cited
# sessions (coordinates only; scenario context is demo text).

SCENARIO eotthbap decodes to eitthvað under its real taps (2026-07-16T22-45-30, wave 30)
# o→i (lean 0.39 toward i), b→v (lean 0.30 toward v), p→ð (edge-key
# undershoot: ð sits right of p, outside the QWERTY motor map). All three
# substitutions are tap-supported, so the margin veto stands aside and the
# 3-sub decode (3.06 nats) fires exactly like the tapless replay — the
# live keyboard had lost it at a per-tap price of 12.4 nats.
T "hann er "
TAP e -0.304 -0.077
TAP o -0.388 -0.351
TAP t -0.425 -0.036
TAP t -0.089 0.083
TAP h 0.442 -0.214
TAP b -0.304 -0.024
TAP a 0.06 0.161
TAP p -0.071 0.357
EXPECT_AUTOCORRECT eitthvað
T " "
EXPECT_LAST_COMMIT eitthvað

